{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17567299","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17567299"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:58:54+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:58:54+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18958"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18958","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18958"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.02,0.1,0.06,0.02,0.79]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11692"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108107"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11692","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11692"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18958"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"90517"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"18"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"4979"},{"type":"tags","id":"4986"},{"type":"tags","id":"4988"},{"type":"tags","id":"4989"},{"type":"tags","id":"4990"},{"type":"tags","id":"5694"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11402"},{"type":"tags","id":"11403"},{"type":"tags","id":"11639"},{"type":"tags","id":"11640"},{"type":"tags","id":"11645"},{"type":"tags","id":"11648"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27508"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27509"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44855"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108107","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/108107"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 68-year-old woman with metastatic breast cancer completes an advance care directive while she has full decision-making capacity. The document is properly witnessed and registered according to state requirements.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the legal status of advance care directives in healthcare?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Can be overridden by family members at any time","Takes effect immediately upon signing","Only applies to end-of-life care decisions","Requires annual renewal to remain valid","Legally binding document that must be followed by healthcare providers"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EAn advance care directive is a \u003Cstrong\u003Elegally binding document that must be followed by healthcare providers\u003C/strong\u003E when a person loses decision-making capacity. It represents the person\u0027s autonomous choices about their future medical care and carries the same legal weight as a contemporaneous decision made by a person with capacity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECan be overridden by family members at any time\u003C/strong\u003E - Family members cannot override a valid advance care directive, though they may be consulted to help interpret the directive\u0027s application to specific situations\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOnly applies to end-of-life care decisions\u003C/strong\u003E - Advance care directives can cover any future healthcare decisions, not just end-of-life care\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERequires annual renewal to remain valid\u003C/strong\u003E - Once properly completed, an advanced care directive remains valid indefinitely unless revoked by the person while they still have capacity\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETakes effect immediately upon signing\u003C/strong\u003E - Advance care directives only take effect when the person loses decision-making capacity\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHealthcare providers must follow the directive\u0027s instructions unless circumstances have changed significantly from those contemplated in the directive or the requested care would be illegal. The person can change or revoke their directive at any time while they maintain decision-making capacity.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Advance care directives are legally binding documents that outline a person\u0027s wishes for future medical care when they lose decision-making capacity.","Advance care directives must be completed while a person has decision-making capacity and can be changed or revoked at any time while capacity remains.","Healthcare providers must follow valid advance care directives unless circumstances have changed significantly or the requested care is illegal."],"references":["Australian Government. Advance care directive. [online]. 2024. [Cited 2025 Jan 21]. Available at: https://www.health.gov.au/topics/palliative-care/planning-your-palliative-care/advance-care-directive","Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"90517"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18958"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"90517","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/90517"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-07-06T20:46:36+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-07-06T20:46:36+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11692"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108107"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false